.SH "NAME"
idioms\-usage \- print a usage message to standard error, then exit
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\f(CR. \fBidioms\fP\fP
.sp
\fBusage\fP \fIMESSAGE\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
\fBusage\fP prints the \fIMESSAGE\fP given to standard error, formatted like so:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
usage: _MESSAGE_
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
and then exits unsuccessfully, error code 22.
